Confusing Miasma			KEY:Granny Drake ~ Confusing Miasma	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.SpecialAttack.Granny DrakeTrait	DESC:A Granny Drake can, as a standard action, exhale a dense, greenish cone of gas. This attack has a range of 40 feet creating a cone 20 feet wide and causes confusion among targets who breathe it in (DC 18 Reflex half duration). The confusion caused by this breath weapon lasts 4 rounds. Targets affected by the Confusing Miasma must roll on the below table to determine their actions.																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.2
Trackless Step			KEY:Granny Drake ~ Trackless Step	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.SpecialQuality.Granny DrakeTrait	DESC:The Granny Drake can move through natural surroundings without leaving a trail and cannot be tracked. A Granny Drake can choose to leave a trail.																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.2
Speed Surge				KEY:Granny Drake ~ Speed Surge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.SpecialQuality.Granny DrakeTrait	DESC:Three times per day as a swift action, a Granny Drake may draw on its draconic heritage for a boost of strength and speed to take an additional move action in that round.																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.2
Forest Sense			KEY:Granny Drake ~ Forest Sense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.SpecialQuality.Granny DrakeTrait	DESC:A Granny Drake can see perfectly well in dense forest conditions, utilizing a combination of keen eyesight and echolocation, and does not take any penalties on Perception checks while in deep woods or forest.																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Elder Care				KEY:Granny Drake ~ Elder Care		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.SpecialQuality.Granny DrakeTrait	DESC:A Granny Drake can choose to impart a small portion of their life essence to another intelligent being. They are attracted almost exclusively to kindly, elderly women, with who they will share this ability. If they so choose, they can permanently lose 2 HP and form a bond with an elderly woman (one over the age of 60). Once this bond is formed, the elderly woman's life span is extended by 1d6 X 10 years beyond her normal span. She heals at twice the normal rate. The two are also psychically bonded. They can, at any distance, share basic emotions. Fear, joy, hunger, curiosity and anger. Only one bond may be formed at any time.															SOURCEPAGE:p.3
